==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Irvingite
<hw>Ir"ving*ite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Eccl.)</fld>
<def>The common designation of a member of a sect founded by the
<person>Rev. Edward Irving</person> (about 1830), who call themselves
the <membof>Catholic Apostolic Church</membof>. They are highly
ritualistic in worship, have an elaborate hierarchy of apostles,
prophets, etc., and look for the speedy coming of Christ.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Is-</ent>⟦br⟧
